                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3974: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-23T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>233. Your 375, September 21, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department is finding it increasingly difficult to explain to American creditors
                    of the Chinese Government the ability of that Government to find funds with
                    which to make payments such as you describe and at the same time fail to make
                    any payment on defaulted loans to Americans, or provision for such payments.</p>
                <p>You may so inform the Chinese Government and say, in addition, that this
                    Government would be glad to receive a statement containing a definite plan on
                    which this Government can rely for the liquidation of the over due
                    obligations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
